This paper is about simplifying a trained neural network through pruning, which is a common technique in machine learning. The paper focuses on the algorithmic and sample complexity aspects of the pruning process, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which is a common application of deep neural networks, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convex optimization, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper deals with neural networks, which are a type of computational model, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and convex analysis, which are common topics in data science, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
